Class ResourceManager

java.lang.Object
org.ziqi.gameEngine.manager.GameManager
org.ziqi.gameEngine.manager.ResourceManager
public class ResourceManager
extends GameManager
ResourceManager class as game manager to take charge of loading, storing and transferring resources when running the game.

  • Constructor Details

    • ResourceManager

      public ResourceManager()
      ResourceManager constructor loads and stores all medias, sprites and background images from resource folder when the GameEngine is launched.
      This will enhance runtime performance when load game levels and switch screens as resources are hold by ResourceManager beforehand.
      See Also:
      loadMediaFromResource(HashMap), loadImagesFromResource(HashMap), loadSpritesFromResource(HashMap)

  • Method Details

    • getLevelSet

      public java.io.InputStream getLevelSet​(java.lang.String setNameInput)
      Loads a set resource as inputStream by given set name from resource folder.
      This method will be called when new game begins or user has chosen one set to begin.
      Parameters:
      setNameInput - String value specifying the set name to be load from resource folder.
      Returns:
      An inputStream of the set resource is returned to caller; If no file is found by given set name, null is returned and message will be logged.
      See Also:
      Utils.SET_NAMES, Utils.getResourcePathAsStream(String)

    • loadImage

      public javafx.scene.image.Image loadImage​(java.lang.String imageName)
      Gets a background image by given image name from HashMap hold by ResourceManager.
      This method will be called when set switching.
      Parameters:
      imageName - String value specifying the background image name.
      Returns:
      The background image is returned by searching from HashMap by given name; If no matches, null is returned.
      See Also:
      Utils.SET_BG_NAMES, m_Images

    • loadSprite

      public javafx.scene.image.Image loadSprite​(java.lang.String spriteName)
      Gets a sprite by given sprite name from HashMap hold by ResourceManager.
      This method will be called when rendering graphicUnit onto gaming screen.
      Parameters:
      spriteName - String value specifying the sprite name described by status of gameObject to be rendered.
      Returns:
      The sprite image is returned by searching from HashMap by given name; If no matches, null is returned.
      See Also:
      m_Sprites, Player.PlayerStatus, Wall.WallStatus, Crate.CrateStatus

    • loadMusic

      public javafx.scene.media.Media loadMusic​(java.lang.String musicName)
      Gets a media by given music name from HashMap hold by ResourceManager.
      Parameters:
      musicName - String value specifying the music name.
      Returns:
      A media is returned by searching from HashMap by given name; If no matches, null is returned.
      See Also:
      MusicManager

    • loadFont

      public java.io.InputStream loadFont​(java.lang.String fontName)
      Gets a inputStream specifying a font resource by given font name.
      Parameters:
      fontName - String value specifying the music name.
      Returns:
      A inputStream to font resource is returned by searching from HashMap by given name; If no matches, null is returned.

    • loadSpritesFromResource

      public void loadSpritesFromResource​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​javafx.scene.image.Image> sprites)
      Loads and stores all sprite images from resource folder for further use.
      This method will only be called with the launching of GameEngine.
      All sprite names are provided by according GameObjects.
      Parameters:
      sprites - A HashMap containing the image resources read from resource folder.
      See Also:
      GameObject, Crate.getSpriteNames(), Diamond.getSpriteNames(), Player.getSpriteNames(), Wall.getSpriteNames()

    • loadMediaFromResource

      public void loadMediaFromResource​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​javafx.scene.media.Media> medias)
      Loads and stores all medias from resource folder for further use.
      This method will only be called with the launching of GameEngine.
      All media names are provided by MusicManager
      Parameters:
      medias - A HashMap containing the media resources read from resource folder.
      See Also:
